  "_comment": [
    "Discogs artist IDs that stand in for 'we don't know who' or 'many people'",
    "rather than for a person or a group. Filtering is ALWAYS by numeric",
    "artist_id -- `name` and `release_count` are documentation, never join keys.",
    "",
    "policy:",
    "  exclude -- the identity never appears in `credit_edges`, so it can never",
    "             be a hop endpoint, a curator suggestion, or a site path node.",
    "  flag    -- the identity stays traversable, but every hop through it is",
    "             tagged `placeholder_artist_hop` and surfaced for human review.",
    "",
    "Everything is `exclude` pending review. Flip an entry to `flag` to soften it;",
    "`default_policy` covers any id added without an explicit policy.",
    "",
    "To re-audit a new snapshot, call CreditGraph.placeholder_artist_candidates(),",
    "which matches names against PLACEHOLDER_NAME_PATTERN and reports whether each",
    "candidate is already listed here. Promotion from candidate to entry is a",
    "human decision: a real band can be named 'Anonymous'.",
    "",
    "release_count is the number of distinct releases the identity is credited on",
    "within the audited one-hop corpus, not the whole Discogs catalog."
  ],
